Checks for any filesystem errors.

inputs\:
diagnosticSoFar - used to chain diagnostics together, and get one report. The output of previous diagnostics, or blank.
freespaceThreshold - minimum acceptable % freespace as a decimal.
host - host to check.
user - username to login to host with.
password - password for user.

Responses\:
success - Diagnostic successful.
failure - something went wrong.
fbddc27f-666b-44f3-a1c6-5da924508d6b.5f2b6d3d-424f-43ff-b9c1-704932b03847.transition.description=memory diagnostics succeeded. fbddc27f-666b-44f3-a1c6-5da924508d6b.61823d4d-d3d7-423e-86fe-d90006f92cdc.prompt=Send email? fbddc27f-666b-44f3-a1c6-5da924508d6b.63119a0f-de05-4c3a-bc6e-90caffe856c2.prompt=Your server diagnostic is\: ${diagnostic} fbddc27f-666b-44f3-a1c6-5da924508d6b.6b630097-6073-424c-931f-f1c08be31988.transition.description=${host} could not be contacted. fbddc27f-666b-44f3-a1c6-5da924508d6b.73668107-1395-4545-bb38-be7ff10c3bd7.transition.description=Network Diagnostics succeeded. fbddc27f-666b-44f3-a1c6-5da924508d6b.74fed087-38fb-4365-9281-6267e4cc8224.description=
Checks for any network errors.

Inputs\:
host - The host to check.
user - The username to login to host with.
password - The password for user.
outputPath - The network accessible path used by the operation to store temporary files. If not specified it points to \\host\admin$\temp\'. If this path is not accessible you should change it to use another share that the host local system account has write access to. By default, the path will have to be  changed on Windows 2000 systems.
diagnostic so far - Used to chain diagnostics together, and get one report. The output of previous diagnostics, or blank.
characterSet - The character encoding of the host computer. The default is UTF-8.

Responses\:
success - Diagnostic successful.
failure - Something went wrong.
connectivity failure - Connection to host may be unreliable.

Note\:
The character encoding specified in the input for characterSet must be compatible for the host and RAS systems, otherwise the command file created to execute the command becomes garbled causing an error while executing.
fbddc27f-666b-44f3-a1c6-5da924508d6b.75784048-a46f-4a86-a11b-e0224b6688b6.description=
Sends an smtp email.
 
Inputs\:
    hostname - The hostname or ip address of the smtp server.
    port - The port smtp service is listening.
    from - From email address.
    to - A delimiter separated list of email address(es) or recipients.
    cc - A delimiter separated list of email address(es) or recipients, to be placed in the CC.
    bcc - A delimiter separated list of email address(es) or recipients, to be placed in the BCC.
    subject - The email subject. If a subject spans on multiple lines, it is formatted to a single one.
    body - The body of the email.
    htmlEmail - Default value is true. The value should be true if the email is in rich text/html format. The value should be false if the email is in plain text format.
    readReceipt - Default is false. The value should be true if read receipt is required, else false.
    attachments - A deliimiter separated list of files to attach (must be full path).
    username - If SMTP authentication is needed, the username to send.
    password - The password to use.
    characterSet - The character set encoding for the entire email which includes subject, body, attached file name and the attached file. Default value is UTF-8.
    contentTransferEncoding - The content transfer encoding scheme (such as 7bit, 8bit, base64, quoted-printable etc) for the entire email which includes subject, body, attached file name and the attached file. Default value is - quoted-printable or Q Encoding.
    delimiter - A delimiter to separate the email recipients and the attachments. This input defaults to ';' if left empty.
 
Responses\:
    success - Successfully sent the email.
    failure - Failed to send the email.

Note\:
1. For special characters (East Asian, right-to-left languages, etc.) you must install the support files on your local machine.
2. For doing this on Windows go to Control Panel -> Regional and Language Options -> Language and check the options at Supplemental language support.
fbddc27f-666b-44f3-a1c6-5da924508d6b.75784048-a46f-4a86-a11b-e0224b6688b6.prompt=The following values are needed to send the email summary. fbddc27f-666b-44f3-a1c6-5da924508d6b.785b2a7e-a671-4f51-9faa-92939ce98396.transition.description=Diagnostic should be emailed. fbddc27f-666b-44f3-a1c6-5da924508d6b.814ece0a-81ca-49df-b8bb-9327b3f7eba0.transition.description=Unable to send diagnostic. fbddc27f-666b-44f3-a1c6-5da924508d6b.88492c6f-d6f9-405b-b416-10238b6832a9.transition.description=running processes diagnostic failed. fbddc27f-666b-44f3-a1c6-5da924508d6b.99c14b93-d47c-4f29-b573-40881a0c12f9.transition.description=running processes diagnostic succeeded. fbddc27f-666b-44f3-a1c6-5da924508d6b.a1afd057-74b3-4812-9089-d1683f5ba9de.transition.description=memory diagnostics failed. fbddc27f-666b-44f3-a1c6-5da924508d6b.b38e94fc-f7b0-440d-bb88-445d30b6f13e.transition.description=CPU Diagnostics succeeded. fbddc27f-666b-44f3-a1c6-5da924508d6b.c38de085-f7c1-45b8-a10c-bbeb8c8df1a0.description=
Executes an Expression (e.x value1 \=\= value2)

Input Parameters\:
value1 - the value to threshold with
value2 - the threshold to threshold against
operator - (\=\=, \!\=,  >, >\=, <, <\=) the type of threshold
okstring - string to push into returnResult if the threshold has not been passed
failedstring - string to push into the returnResult if the threshold has been passed

Responses\:
true - the expression is true
fales - the expression is false
fbddc27f-666b-44f3-a1c6-5da924508d6b.cb8c8420-5a94-4f26-85b3-a727eef81594.prompt=Enter the email "to" address\: fbddc27f-666b-44f3-a1c6-5da924508d6b.description=
This flow attempts to diagnose a problem with a windows server.

Inputs\:
host - The server to check the health of.
user - the username to use when authenticating with the host. Not necessary for localhost.
password - The password to use when authenticating with the host. Not necessary for localhost.
mailHost - The address of an SMTP server to use when sending the email.
mailUsername - If SMTP authentication is needed, the username to send.
mailPassword - If SMTP authentication is needed, the password to use.
to - The email address to send the server health summary to.
from - The email address the summary will appear to come from.
characterSet - The character set encoding for the entire email which includes subject, body, attached file name and the attached file. Default value is UTF-8.
contentTransferEncoding - The content transfer encoding scheme (such as 7bit, 8bit, base64, quoted-printable etc) for the entire email which includes subject, body, attached file name and the attached file. Default value is - quoted-printable or Q Encoding.
sendEmail - Whether an email will be sent containing the summary (if no email is sent, they are displayed to screen).
freeMemoryThreshold - % of total memory that should not be in use as a decimal.
freePagingThreshold - Number of kilobytes of paging file expected to not be in use.
maxPagesPerSecond - Maximum \# of memory pages per second considered acceptable.
minimumTotalMemory - A minimum value of memory that this computer is expected to have.
max_blocked_threads - maximum acceptable \# of blocked threads.
CPU Usage threshold - Maximum acceptable % cpu usage.
freespace threshold - minimum acceptable % freespace as a decimal.
process_list - A list of processes that should be running.
outputPath - network accessible path used by the operation to store temporary files. If not specified it points to \\host\admin$\temp\'. If this     path is not accessible you should change it to use another share that the host local system account has write access to. By default, the path will have to be  changed on Windows 2000 systems

Responses\:
success - Diagnostic successful.
failure - something went wrong.
